00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,360
格兰特 倘若这世界没有时间多愁善感...
If it's going to be a world with no time for sentiment Grant...

171
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:43,890
...那么这也不会是我想要生活的世界
...the it's not a world that I want to live in.

172
00:20:27,610 --> 00:20:29,040
"夏去夏来天鹅死"
After Many a Summer

173
00:20:29,050 --> 00:20:30,820
(英国作家赫胥黎在1939年所写小说)
Dies the Swan.

174
00:20:35,650 --> 00:20:36,970
想必大家...
I think you've all...

175
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:39,640
...都读过
...read the Huxley novel

176
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:41,790
我三周前布置的这本赫胥黎的小说了吧
I assigned more than three weeks ago?

177
00:20:45,590 --> 00:20:47,340
题目与作品有何关联?
How does the title relate to our story?

178
00:20:48,540 --> 00:20:49,440
蒙先生 请讲
Yes, Mr. Mong.

179
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:50,680
并无关联(赫胥黎引用"泰索尼斯"中的诗句)
It doesn't.

180
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,290
讲述了一个富翁
It's about a rich guy

181
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:55,270
觉得自己已是垂暮 配不上那个女孩...
who's too afraid that he's too old for this girl...

182
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,910
...而他认为年轻的男人...
...and thinks that a young guy...

183
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:25,880
拉斯
Russ.

184
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:38,020
拉斯?
Russ?

185
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:57,760
请讲 赫希先生
Yes, Mr. Hirsch.

186
00:21:58,460 --> 00:22:01,730
先生 在第79页 普罗普特先生说道...
Sir, on page 79, Mr. Propter says that...

187
00:22:01,740 --> 00:22:03,430
...圣经中最愚蠢的章节就是
...the stupidest text in the Bible is

188
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,470
"他们无故地恨我"(约翰福音15:25)
they hated me without a cause.

189
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,740
这是为纳粹对犹太人的憎恶开脱吗?
Does that mean the Nazis were right to hate the Jews?

190
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:10,040
难道赫胥黎是一名反犹分子吗?      不
Is Huxley an anti-Semite?        No.

191
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:21,040
不 赫胥黎先生并非反犹
No, Mr. Huxley is not an anti-Semite.

192
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,850
而且 纳粹对犹太的民族仇恨是天大的错误
Of course, the Nazis were wrong to hate the Jews.

193
00:22:23,860 --> 00:22:25,970
但他们对犹太人的恨并非无缘无故
But their hating the Jews was not without a cause.

194
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,560
只是这原因并不真实存在
It's just that the cause wasn't real.

195
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:32,890
憎恨的原因源于人们的臆想
The cause was imagined.

196
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:35,990
真正的原因是恐惧
The cause was fear.

197
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,760
咱们先暂且不要谈论犹太的问题
Let's leave the Jews out o this just for a moment.

198
00:22:41,470 --> 00:22:43,490
想想另一个少数派群体 那种...
Let's think of another minority. One that...

199
00:22:44,510 --> 00:22:46,270
那种被人视而不见的少数派
One that can go unnoticed if it needs to.

200
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,790
其实这世上有着各种各样的少数派
There are all sorts of minorities,

201
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,810
譬如金发的人...
blondes for example...

202
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:54,890
...长着雀斑的人
...or people with freckles.

203
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:58,550
但是只有在少数派对多数派构成威胁时...
But a minority is only thought of as one...

204
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:01,800
...他们才被称之为少数派
...when it constitutes some kind of threat to the majority.

205
00:23:01,810 --> 00:23:04,100
是真实的 还是臆想的
A real threat or an imagined one.

206
00:23:04,110 --> 00:23:06,770
这当中便产生了恐惧
And therein lies the fear.

207
00:23:09,010 --> 00:23:11,180
倘若少数派不为人知被人忽略
If the minority is somehow invisible...

208
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:15,790
...那么恐惧便无限放大
...and the fear is much greater.

209
00:23:17,490 --> 00:23:20,410
恐惧的存在 导致少数派被迫害
That fear is why the minority is persecuted.

210
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:22,000
所以 你们看原因总是存在的
So, you see there always is a cause.

211
00:23:22,070 --> 00:23:23,190
这原因便是恐惧
The cause is fear.

212
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,020
少数派其实就是普通人
Minorities are just people.

213
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:28,150
如我们一样的普通人
People like us.

214
00:23:35,010 --> 00:23:36,650
感觉好像把你们讲糊涂了
I can see that I've lost you a bit.

215
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:41,350
这样吧 咱们今天先不讲赫胥黎了...
So tell you what? We're gonna forget about Mr. Huxley today...

216
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:43,850
...我们来探讨一下恐惧
...and we're gonna talk about fear.

217
00:23:44,870 --> 00:23:47,190
毕竟...恐惧才是我们真正的敌人
Fear, after all, is our real enemy.

218
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,920
恐惧正在吞噬着我们的世界
Fear is taking over our world.

219
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:53,750
恐惧被用来操控着我们的社会
Fear is being used as a tool of manipulation in our society.

220
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:56,110
这就是政客们玩弄的伎俩
It's how politicians peddle policy.

221
00:23:57,230 --> 00:23:58,710
这也就是麦迪逊大道上总有人卖给我们
It's how Madison Avenue sells us

222
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:00,140
不需要的东西
things that we don't need.

223
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:01,280
仔细想想看
Think about it.

224
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,350
对被袭的恐惧
Fear of being attacked.

225
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:08,160
恐惧着某个暗处隐藏着共产主义者
Fear of that there are communists lurking around every corner.

226
00:24:08,980 --> 00:24:10,800
恐惧着那些和我们生活习惯截然不同的...
Fear of that some little Caribbean country...

227
00:24:10,810 --> 00:24:12,250
...中美洲国家会对我们
...that doesn't believe in our way of life

228
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:13,390
造成威胁(古巴危机)
poses a threat to us.

229
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,770
恐惧着黑人的文化将会统领全世界
Fear that black culture may take over the world.

230
00:24:15,780 --> 00:24:18,150
担心猫王的屁股哪天会晃掉下来
Fear of Elvis Presley's hips.

231
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,930
事实上 这个很有可能成为现实
Actually, maybe that one is a real fear.

232
00:24:24,850 --> 00:24:27,550
恐惧着口臭会破坏我们的友谊
Fear that our bad breath might ruin our friendships.

233
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:33,280
恐惧着韶华逝去孑然一身
Fear of growing old and being alone.

234
00:24:40,390 --> 00:24:43,800
恐惧着自己一无是处 无人问津
The of that we're useless and that no one cares what we have to say.

235
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:49,600
周末愉快
Have a good weekend.

236
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:58,510
先生! 我能跟你谈谈吗?
Sir! May I talk to you for a minute?

237
00:24:59,620 --> 00:25:01,550
为什么你之前没有这样跟我们讲过呢?
Why don't you always talk to us like that?

238
00:25:01,660 --> 00:25:03,170
我怕你们不爱听
I don't think it went over very well.

239
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:05,890
老师 我经常会有对周遭的恐惧
Man, fear of things gets to me all the time.

240
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:08,890
但你无法跟别人倾诉 否则会让别人觉得你很傻
But you can't talk about it with anyone or you just sound like a fool.

241
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:10,540
连跟洛伊斯都不能倾诉吗?
You can't even talk about it with Lois?

242
00:25:10,890 --> 00:25:12,710
我觉得她什么都不怕
I don't think she's afraid of anything.

243
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:14,230
每个人都有恐惧的东西 肯尼
Everyone's afraid of something, Kenny.

244
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:15,850
先生 那你怕什么?
What are you afraid of, sir?

245
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:17,430
车
Cars.

246
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:20,570
你住在洛杉矶 怎么能怕车呢?
How can you live in Los Angeles and be afraid of cars?

247
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:21,770
可能不能吧
Maybe you can't.

248
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:25,840
有时候 我内心的恐惧会让我慌张无力
Sometimes my fear of things can almost paralyze me.

249
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,030
内心纠结紧张
It's like I get really panic stricken

250
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,020
生怕自己的感情会突然爆发
and I feel like I might explode or something.

251
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,200
我能问您个私人问题吗 先生?
May I ask you a personal question, sir?

252
00:25:33,210 --> 00:25:34,140
随便
If you like.

253
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:36,270
你曾经嗨过吗?
Do you ever get high?

254
00:25:37,490 --> 00:25:39,040
你觉得我都多大岁数了?
How old do I look to you?

255
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,800
那您之前吸过毒吗?
Have you ever taken any drugs?

256
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:43,110
当然 肯尼
Of course, Kenny.

257
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:44,950
譬如什么?
Like what?

258
00:25:45,910 --> 00:25:46,970
波特先生 我觉得
I don't feel I should be discussing

259
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:49,260
在校园讨论这事情有点不合适吧
this with you on campus Mr. Potter.

260
00:25:49,580 --> 00:25:51,330
这是我解压的唯一方式
It's the only way I get by sometimes.

261
00:25:52,630 --> 00:25:53,910
那您试过迷幻药吗?
Have you ever tried mescaline?

262
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,670
倒不是我的首选
Not my drug of choice.

263
00:25:55,970 --> 00:25:57,680
有次吸完 我把半边眉毛都刮掉了
I shaved off one of my eyebrows once on mescaline.

264
00:25:57,690 --> 00:25:59,170
看上去不好看
Not a good look for me.

265
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,590
先生?      我对着镜子
Sir?        I looked in the mirror.

266
00:26:02,180 --> 00:26:03,690
吸完迷幻药看镜子是个错误至极的选择
Big mistake if you're high on mescaline.

267
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:06,440
我感觉我的眉毛要把整个脸都吞噬了
I decided that my eyebrows were taking over my face.

268
00:26:06,450 --> 00:26:07,770
所以我就刮掉了一半
Before I knew it, I had shaved one off.

269
00:26:07,780 --> 00:26:08,790
我等眉毛长出来的时候
I wore a band-aid over my eye

270
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,530
被迫贴了六周的创可贴
for about six weeks while my brow grew back.

271
00:26:10,540 --> 00:26:11,370
非常尴尬
Very embarrassing.

272
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:13,380
打那以后你就再没碰过了?
You didn't take it again after that?

273
00:26:13,490 --> 00:26:14,510
肯尼 你有听我说话吗?
Kenny, have you been listening to me?

274
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,510
我把眉毛都剃掉了啊
I shaved off my eyebrow.

275
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,430
我只是想要体验一下 波特先生
I wanted an experience Mr. Potter,

276
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:20,100
又不是想当台上的小丑
not a career on stage.

277
00:26:23,660 --> 00:26:26,040
先生 你什么时候想要嗨一下的话 我这儿有货
If you ever want to get high sir, I usually have some dope.

278
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,940
你还真是疯了
You're really mad aren't you?

279
00:26:35,670 --> 00:26:36,320
抱歉 先生
I'm sorry, sir.

280
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,840
或许这种交谈让你觉得不适
I guess you don't feel very comfortable talking like this.

281
00:26:38,850 --> 00:26:40,110
此话怎讲?
What makes you say that?

282
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:43,600
洛伊斯觉得你过于小心谨慎了 就像今早...
Lois thinks you're kind of cagey. Like this morning...

283
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:44,430
...你不动声色地听
...when you were listening to

284
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,610
我们高谈阔论赫胥黎
all that crap we were talking about Huxley.

285
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:47,920
也不是所有人啊
Well, not all of you.

286
00:26:47,930 --> 00:26:49,780
我记得你不是没有开口吗
I didn't notice you open your mouth once.

287
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:50,990
因为我在注视您
I was watching you.

288
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,590
你总是先让我们发表见解
You let us ramble on and on

289
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,600
然后你再直言不讳地解释
and then you straighten us out.

290
00:26:56,580 --> 00:26:59,200
你却从未主动告诉过我们你所认为的一切
But you never really tell us everything you know about something.

291
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:03,340
或许在一定程度上 你说得没错
Well, maybe that's true up to a point.

292
00:27:04,700 --> 00:27:06,390
但这并不是我故意谨慎
It's not that I want to be cagey.

293
00:27:07,540 --> 00:27:11,450
只是我真的无法将所有都放开谈论
It's just that I can't really discuss things completely openly...

294
00:27:11,460 --> 00:27:12,170
...尤其是在学校
...at school.

295
00:27:13,290 --> 00:27:14,760
有人会误会的
Someone would misunderstand.

296
00:27:16,660 --> 00:27:19,150
就像我今天试过了 反响不是很好啊
I tried that today. It didn't really work out.

297
00:27:25,970 --> 00:27:27,590
你是想来买什么吗 先生?
What was it you wanted to get, sir?

298
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:29,850
没什么 我是刚好要去院长办公室
Nothing. I was on my way to the dean's office.

299
00:27:30,270 --> 00:27:33,210
所以你走了这么长的路就是为了跟我讲话咯?
You mean you walked all the way down here just to talk to me?

300
00:27:33,790 --> 00:27:35,140
是啊      那么...
Why not?        Well...

301
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:37,170
先生 我觉得我应该好好答谢你才是了
I think you deserve something for that, sir.

302
00:27:38,180 --> 00:27:39,390
看看吧 选一个 先生
Here sir, take your pick.

303
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:43,450
我送给您      谢谢
It's on me.        Thank you.

304
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,340
我还以为你会选蓝色
I thought you'd probably pick blue.

305
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:49,960
为什么是蓝色?
Why blue?

306
00:27:49,970 --> 00:27:51,910
蓝色不是代表着灵性吗?
Isn't blue supposed to be spiritual?

307
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,680
为什么你觉得我会有灵性?
What makes you think I'm spiritual?

308
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:58,580
你呢? 红色?
And you? Red?

309
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:03,160
红色代表什么?      那可太多了
What is red stand for?        A lot of things.

310
00:28:03,170 --> 00:28:04,820
愤怒 欲望
Rage, lust.

311
00:28:06,430 --> 00:28:07,210
开玩笑吧啊?
No kidding?

312
00:28:13,090 --> 00:28:14,040
那么 先生 我...
Well sir, I...

313
00:28:15,030 --> 00:28:16,210
咱们再会啊
I guess I see you around.

314
00:29:35,270 --> 00:29:36,330
喂?
Hello?

315
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:37,860
小淘气 你在干嘛呢啊?
What are you up to, kiddo?

316
00:29:37,870 --> 00:29:41,310
正想要读本书 你今天过得如何啊?
Just trying to finish up a book. How's your day going?

317
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:42,220
不错
Fine.

318
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:43,540
我刚好要下班了
I was just leaving school

319
00:29:43,540 --> 00:29:45,500
想问问你今晚需不需要带点东西
and wanted to know if you needed anything for tonight.

320
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:48,960
谢谢 你可真贴心
Thanks, you're sweet.

321
00:29:49,100 --> 00:29:50,190
不过我好像不缺什么
But I think I'm all set.

322
00:29:52,300 --> 00:29:53,470
你如果能...
Be a darling and...

323
00:29:53,480 --> 00:29:56,590
...买点杜松子酒就更好了 唐桂来牌的吧
...pick up gin for me, Tangueray.

324
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,240
我喜欢瓶子的颜色
I love the color of the bottle.

325
00:29:59,180 --> 00:30:02,210
你是喜欢瓶子里边的东西 你想要我几点到?
You love what's in it. What time do you want me?

326
00:30:02,930 --> 00:30:05,770
要是方便的话 7点钟最好了
7 would be great if that's ok with you.

327
00:30:05,890 --> 00:30:07,950
那好 到时见了
Perfect. I'll see you then.

328
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:10,040
到时见 再见了 乔
I'll see you then. Bye, Geo.

329
00:30:10,050 --> 00:30:11,050
再见 小淘气
Bye, kiddo.

330
00:30:32,660 --> 00:30:34,260
很美
Beautiful.

331
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:28,490
波特先生 什么事?
Yes, Mr. Potter?

332
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:29,970
您要去哪儿吗 先生?
Are you going somewhere, sir?

333
00:31:30,550 --> 00:31:32,840
人们开车不都是为了去哪儿吗?
That is usually why people get into their cars.

334
00:31:32,850 --> 00:31:35,070
不 我是说 你是要去度假或是什么吗?
No, I mean are you going on vacation or something?

335
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:35,850
什么?
What?

336
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:37,630
我看您把办公室都清理干净了?
I saw you cleaning out your office.

337
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:45,160
肯尼 你到底想要干嘛?
What exactly is it that you want, Kenny?

338
00:31:46,870 --> 00:31:47,930
我只是想说
I was just hoping that perhaps

339
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:50,320
找个时间 咱们可以喝一杯
we could get together for a drink or something sometime.

340
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,290
为什么这么说?
Why is that?

341
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:54,880
我也不清楚 先生
I don't know, sir.

342
00:31:56,070 --> 00:31:58,570
可能我觉得你会喜欢这样 而且...
Because I think you might like it. And...

343
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:01,380
...感觉您现在需要一个朋友的陪伴
...because you seem as though you could use a friend.

344
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:03,740
哦 是吗?      是的 先生 您需要
Oh really?        Yes, sir. You do.

345
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:09,600
或许你说得对
They may be right.

346
00:32:11,530 --> 00:32:13,410
下次找机会吧 我赶时间
It will have to be another time. I'm late.

347
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:16,950
不过谢谢你的诚挚邀请
But thank you for the invitation.

348
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:19,680
也谢谢你今早的那番话
And thank you for the talk earlier.

349
00:32:21,450 --> 00:32:22,930
别再碰迷幻药了
And stay away from the mescaline.

350
00:32:55,030 --> 00:32:56,410
您好 福克纳先生
Hello, Mr. Falconer.

351
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:58,540
嗯 你好吗?      很好 先生
Hello. How are you today?        I'm fine, sir.

352
00:32:58,550 --> 00:33:00,890
您需要拿保险箱出来吗?      是的
Do you need to get into your box?        Yes, I do.

353
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:02,100
请跟我来
Follow me.

354
00:33:10,780 --> 00:33:11,840
给您 先生
Here you are, sir.

355
00:33:14,270 --> 00:33:15,860
麻烦请您在这里签名...
If you could please sign here...

356
00:33:24,590 --> 00:33:25,500
谢谢      谢谢
Thank you.        Thank you.

357
00:34:30,870 --> 00:34:32,760
跟我讲讲你那朋友 夏洛特
So explain your friend Charlotte to me.

358
00:34:34,310 --> 00:34:35,650
你都想知道什么?
What would you like to know?

359
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:39,010
我也不知道 听起来你们关系很亲密
I don't know. You seem very intimate I guess.

360
00:34:39,940 --> 00:34:41,900
感觉你们之前曾经是恋人
Like you were once together or something.

361
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,930
你没跟她睡过吗?      睡过
You haven't slept with her, have you?        Yes.

362
00:34:48,770 --> 00:34:49,470
然后呢?
And?

363
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,070
年轻的时候 一时冲动睡过几次
A few times when we were young.

364
00:34:53,350 --> 00:34:55,040
当然 这不可能对我毫无意义
I wouldn't say that it meant nothing to me...

365
00:34:55,050 --> 00:34:57,120
...不过显然这对夏莉的意义非比寻常
...but it certainly meant a great deal more to Charley.

366
00:34:57,660 --> 00:34:59,660
那是很久之前在伦敦的事了
It was a long time ago in London.

367
00:35:01,650 --> 00:35:02,820
我很爱夏莉
I love Charley.

368
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:05,620
我们是很好的朋友 就这样
And We were very close friends but that's all.

369
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:06,790
这我倒不明白了
Well, I'm confused.

370
00:35:07,770 --> 00:35:09,690
如果你和女人上床 那你为什么跟我在一起?
If you sleep with women then why are you with me?

371
00:35:09,700 --> 00:35:11,440
因为我会爱上男人
Because I fall in love with men.

372
00:35:11,450 --> 00:35:13,360
因为我爱上了你
Because I fell in love with you.

373
00:35:16,500 --> 00:35:18,640
再说了 谁没在年轻时候 跟女人睡过啊?
Anyway, doesn't everyone sleep with women when they're young?

374
00:35:18,650 --> 00:35:20,960
我没有      你开玩笑
I haven't.        You're joking.

375
00:35:20,970 --> 00:35:22,200
不 我没开玩笑
No, I'm not.

376
00:35:23,210 --> 00:35:25,070
感觉我好像对什么都不感兴趣
It was just never anything that interested me.

377
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:25,900
你还真是新潮啊
Well, you're awfully

378
00:35:25,910 --> 00:35:27,110
(50-60年代青年人对世事不关心的态度)
modern aren't you?

379
00:35:27,690 --> 00:35:29,990
你知道吗 这也是我最初注意到你的一点...
You know, I think that was the first thing that I noticed about you...

380
00:35:31,980 --> 00:35:33,850
...就是你的自信
...was how sure of yourself you were.

381
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:38,990
你这么年轻怎会对一切都如此笃定?
How can you be so sure about everything at your age?

382
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:42,180
你觉得我真的了解自己吗?
You think I'm sure of myself?

383
00:35:42,950 --> 00:35:43,930
当然
Of course, you are.

384
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,140
我弄好了 谢谢你
I'm finished now. Thank you.

385
00:36:13,060 --> 00:36:14,230
福克纳先生?
Yes, Mr. Falconer?

386
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,290
还有什么需要效劳的吗?
Is there something else we can help you with today?

387
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:19,890
我找不到支票簿了 需要些现金
I can't find my check book and I need some cash.

388
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:23,230
真是运气不佳啊 请稍等一会儿
Not my day I'm afraid. Excuse me a minute.

389
00:37:14,970 --> 00:37:17,680
妈妈说浓眉的人太俗气
Mommy says bushy eyebrows are pedestrian,

390
00:37:17,690 --> 00:37:19,050
我觉得你的浓眉很漂亮
but I think yours are pretty.

391
00:37:20,140 --> 00:37:21,910
你的也很漂亮啊
I think yours are pretty too.

392
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,980
为何你看上去这么伤心?
Why do you look so sad?

393
00:37:23,990 --> 00:37:26,110
你想要见见查尔斯・赫斯顿吗?
Would you like to meet Charlton Heston?

394
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:28,830
宾虚
Ben Hur.

395
00:37:31,410 --> 00:37:32,760
我说的是我的蝎子
He's our scorpion.

396
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:36,780
每晚喂它不同的食物 看着它把它们杀死
Every night we throw in something new to him and watch him kill it.

397
00:37:37,230 --> 00:37:39,110
爸爸说就像是看角斗一样
Daddy says it's like the colosseum.

398
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:41,770
所以我哥哥汤姆就弄了些圆柱放进来
So my brother Tom put on all the columns in here.

399
00:37:42,430 --> 00:37:44,130
他想当个布景师
He wants to be a set designer.

400
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:46,240
它还没有吃掉那只蜘蛛...
He hasn't eaten the spider yet...

401
00:37:46,250 --> 00:37:49,130
...因为他还没有消化完昨晚喂它的那只飞蛾
...cause he's still full from the moth we gave him last night.

402
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:52,410
爸爸说他想把你放进角斗场去
Daddy says he wants to throw you in to the colosseum.

403
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:55,290
不是吧? 为什么呢?
No kidding? Why?

404
00:37:55,830 --> 00:37:57,410
他说你是穿拖鞋的(暗指他是同性恋)
He says you're light in your loafers...

405
00:37:57,420 --> 00:37:59,780
可你根本没穿拖鞋
...but you aren't even wearing loafers.

406
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:02,250
我觉得我哥哥汤姆也是个穿拖鞋的...
I think my brother Tom is light in his loafers too...

407
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:04,730
...可他穿的是凯兹牌(帆布鞋)
...but he wears Keds.

408
00:38:05,860 --> 00:38:10,510
他让我用鸡蛋给头发做护理
He made me do a hair conditioning treatment on my hair with eggs.

409
00:38:11,100 --> 00:38:12,500
看上去有光泽吗?
Does it look shiny?

410
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:15,200
甜心 你怎么在这里打搅福克纳先生呢?
Sweetheart, what are you doing bothering Mr. Falconer?

411
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:18,350
苏珊 她没有打扰到我 你好啊
She's not bothering me at all Susan. How are you?

412
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:20,460
乔治 很高兴见到你
I'm glad to see you George.

413
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:23,700
乔治 我们今晚请了些人来喝酒...
George, we're having a few people over tonight for drinks...

414
00:38:23,710 --> 00:38:25,670
...如果你能过来 大家一定很开心
...and would love to have you join us if you could.

415
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:27,820
谢谢你的好意 不过我另外有事了
Thank you. That's very kind of you but I have plans.

416
00:38:29,010 --> 00:38:30,330
那就下次吧
Another time then.

417
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:33,400
珍妮弗 咱们别打扰福克纳先生了
Jennifer, let's let Mr. Falconer get back to his banking.

418
00:38:33,410 --> 00:38:34,350
乔治 再见
Goodbye, George.

419
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:36,340
再见 苏珊 再见 珍妮弗
Bye, Susan. Bye, Jennifer.

420
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,630
先生 需要点什么吗?
May I help you, sir?

421
00:38:47,180 --> 00:38:49,280
我想买这把枪用的子弹 谢谢
I'd like to buy some bullets for this gun, please.

422
00:38:49,290 --> 00:38:52,810
嗯 先生 这把枪可是有年头了啊
Yes, sir. This is a really old gun, sir.

423
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:54,890
我们正在搞促销 买二赠送一把手枪
We have a two for one sale on handguns at the moment.

424
00:38:54,900 --> 00:38:56,380
要不要买一把送给女士呢?
Perhaps one for the little lady?

425
00:38:56,390 --> 00:38:57,950
不必了 我只要子弹就好了
No thank you. Just the bullets, please.

426
00:39:01,070 --> 00:39:02,510
给您 还需要点什么吗?
Here you go. Anything else?

427
00:39:03,030 --> 00:39:03,900
不用了 谢谢
No, thank you.

428
00:39:03,910 --> 00:39:05,530
一共2块29分 先生
That would be $2.29, sir.

429
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:09,900
谢谢
Thank you.

430
00:39:46,430 --> 00:39:49,200
抱歉 但愿她没冲你乱吠吧
I'm sorry. I hope she didn't growl at you.

431
00:39:49,210 --> 00:39:51,740
她有时会有些失控 所以我把她放在车里
She goes a little crazy sometimes when I have to leave her in the car.

432
00:39:51,750 --> 00:39:53,270
她很漂亮 叫什么名字?
She's perfect. What's her name?

433
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:54,390
印蒂雅
India.

434
00:39:55,260 --> 00:39:56,130
过去
Let's go there.

435
00:40:01,410 --> 00:40:02,330
来 小可爱
You little baby.

436
00:40:06,220 --> 00:40:09,910
我之前也养过猎狐犬 这种狗不怎么常见
I used to have smooth fox terriers. You don't see them very often.

437
00:40:30,410 --> 00:40:32,230
这狗闻起来像是奶油吐司
The very smell of buttered toast.

438
00:40:33,390 --> 00:40:34,640
她还是个小狗 对吧?
She's still a puppy isn't she?

439
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:41,710
那么
Well.

440
00:40:41,720 --> 00:40:43,750
祝您晚上愉快     你也是
Have a nice evening.        You too.

441
00:40:44,410 --> 00:40:45,410
晚安 印蒂雅
Good night, India.

442
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,910
真不好意思      没关系的
I'm sorry about that.        No, It's ok.

443
00:41:01,340 --> 00:41:02,940
是我的错 我再给你买包烟
It's my fault. I'll get you another pack.

444
00:41:03,270 --> 00:41:04,400
没关系的
It's ok. Don't worry.

445
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:06,690
不 不 我还是买吧
No, no I insist.

446
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:12,410
谢谢
Thank you.

447
00:41:13,220 --> 00:41:14,530
谢谢 抱歉在门口打烂了瓶子
I'm sorry about the broken glass.

448
00:41:15,230 --> 00:41:16,920
给你      谢谢了 伙计
Here you go.        Thanks man.

449
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:19,980
要来一根吗?
You want one?

450
00:41:21,100 --> 00:41:21,780
不 谢谢
No, thanks.

451
00:41:23,890 --> 00:41:25,870
算了 来一根又有何妨嘛
Actually, yes. Why not?

452
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:27,250
谢谢
Thank you.

453
00:41:57,890 --> 00:41:59,650
卡洛斯      你说什么?
Carlos.        What did you say?

454
00:41:59,660 --> 00:42:02,150
卡洛斯 你问我的名字嘛
Carlos. You asked me my name.

455
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,280
你没事吧
Are you okay?

456
00:42:05,380 --> 00:42:06,060
哦 没事
Yeah.

457
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:07,850
嗯 抱歉
Yeah, I'm sorry.

458
00:42:12,100 --> 00:42:13,880
(西语)你真是棱角分明
You're really something.

459
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:15,680
脸庞犹如雕塑
You have an incredible face.

460
00:42:16,500 --> 00:42:18,230
好好利用 这是上天的恩赐
Enjoy that. It's a great gift.

461
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:20,520
你的西班牙语很不错
Your Spanish is perfect.

462
00:42:20,530 --> 00:42:21,330
谢谢
Thank you.

463
00:42:25,290 --> 00:42:26,850
你应该更加好好珍惜你的外表
I should have used it more.

464
00:42:27,950 --> 00:42:28,620
其实...
Well...

465
00:42:29,240 --> 00:42:30,130
现在也不算晚
It's not too late.

466
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,170
你要干嘛?
What are you doing?

467
00:42:59,350 --> 00:43:00,680
不是要去什么地方吗?
Aren't we going somewhere?

468
00:43:01,830 --> 00:43:04,620
不 不过 谢谢你
No. But, thanks.

469
00:43:09,550 --> 00:43:10,170
是烟雾
You know, it's the smog

470
00:43:10,180 --> 00:43:11,590
造就了夕阳的余晖(洛杉矶的光化学烟雾)
that makes it that color.

471
00:43:12,670 --> 00:43:14,780
我从未见过这样的天空
I've never seen a sky like this before.

472
00:43:16,370 --> 00:43:19,360
有时候 丑陋也有自己独特之美
Sometimes awful things have their own kind of beauty.

473
00:43:24,690 --> 00:43:26,320
我能再来一根吗?
Could I have another cigarette?

474
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:27,620
当然
Sure.

475
00:43:55,010 --> 00:43:57,660
你确定不想去兜兜风吗?      我确定
Are sure that you don't want to go for a drive?        I'm sure.

476
00:44:00,970 --> 00:44:02,990
你从哪儿来?      马德里
Where are you from?        Madrid.

477
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:05,530
马德里? 你是怎么来这里的
Madrid? How did you get here?

478
00:44:06,130 --> 00:44:07,260
说来话长
It's a long story.

479
00:44:07,930 --> 00:44:10,110
我在工作的旅店认识了一个洛杉矶来的小伙子...
I met a guy from LA at the hotel where I worked...

480
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:10,890
...他告诉我
...who told me

481
00:44:10,900 --> 00:44:14,300
我可以跟他住 他可以给我找份工作
I could live with him and that he could get me an agent.

482
00:44:14,310 --> 00:44:16,450
但他没想过 我有西班牙口音
But he never realized that I have a Spanish accent.

483
00:44:17,750 --> 00:44:21,210
我喜欢你的口音 你说起来非常动听
I like your accent. You speak very well.

484
00:44:22,750 --> 00:44:24,060
你怎么学的英语?
How did you learn English?

485
00:44:24,980 --> 00:44:27,600
我小时候 妈妈有个美国男友
My mom had an American boyfriend when I was little.

486
00:44:27,710 --> 00:44:29,110
你妈妈现在在马德里吗?
Is your mother in Madrid?

487
00:44:30,140 --> 00:44:32,080
嗯 是的 她是理发师
Yes, she is. She cuts hair.

488
00:44:32,090 --> 00:44:33,910
她在我走之前 为我剪了头发
She cut my hair before I left.

489
00:44:34,310 --> 00:44:35,410
你喜欢这发型吗?
Do you like it?

490
00:44:36,580 --> 00:44:38,540
我觉得 我看起来像詹姆斯・迪恩
I thought it made me look like James Dean.

491
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:40,110
你比詹姆斯・迪恩还好看
You are better than James Dean.

492
00:44:40,820 --> 00:44:41,740
真的?
Really?

493
00:44:41,750 --> 00:44:42,660
承蒙夸奖
Thanks.

494
00:44:47,210 --> 00:44:49,870
从没有人跟我搭讪却对我毫无企图
No one has ever picked me up and not wanted something.

495
00:44:50,430 --> 00:44:51,810
我觉得是你找我搭讪的吧
I think you picked me up.

496
00:44:53,570 --> 00:44:55,370
今天对我来说是相对烦恼的一天
This is kind of a serious day for me.

497
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:59,520
说说看 像你这样的人怎会有烦恼?
Come on. What could be so serious for a guy like you?

498
00:45:02,620 --> 00:45:04,570
我是想要忘却一位旧爱
I'm just trying to get over an old love I guess.

499
00:45:07,330 --> 00:45:09,580
我妈妈说 爱人就像是公共汽车
My mother says that lovers are like buses.

500
00:45:09,590 --> 00:45:12,980
只要你耐心等待 下一辆自然会来
You just have to wait a little while and another one comes along.

501
00:45:18,830 --> 00:45:19,750
我得走了
I have to go.

502
00:45:21,690 --> 00:45:22,800
你是个不错的人
You're a nice guy.

503
00:45:23,110 --> 00:45:24,490
希望你能够找到...
I hope you find...

504
00:45:24,500 --> 00:45:25,790
...和你一样的人
...someone like you.

505
00:45:26,680 --> 00:45:27,380
谢谢
Thanks.

506
00:45:28,410 --> 00:45:29,390
我先走了
I'm going away.

507
00:46:25,610 --> 00:46:27,280
轮到你去换了
It's your turn to change it.

508
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:30,180
才不要 是轮到你了
Yeah, I'm not changing it. It's your turn.

509
00:46:31,220 --> 00:46:32,730
再说了 我放什么你都不喜欢的
Besides, you never like what I put on anyway.

510
00:46:32,740 --> 00:46:35,240
我付你五块钱去换 我太老了 站不起来
I'll give you five dollars if you change it. I'm too old to get up.

511
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,660
你只有在能占便宜的时候才倚老卖老
You're only old when it's convenient for you to be old.

512
00:46:38,140 --> 00:46:39,350
你在读什么呀
What are you reading anyway?

513
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:40,230
变形记 卡夫卡著
Metamorphosis

514
00:46:41,080 --> 00:46:43,010
老天 又是那些无病呻吟的狗屎
Oh God. Not that depressing crap again.

515
00:46:43,020 --> 00:46:44,210
上课用的
It's for my class.

516
00:46:45,990 --> 00:46:48,610
你读的又是什么高级小说啊
What highbrow work of fiction might you be reading?

517
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:50,060
蒂凡尼的早餐 卡波特著
Breakfast at Tiffany's

