这对女人来说没那么容易的
It's not as easy for a woman.

689
01:03:29,940 --> 01:03:31,680
所有事我都竭尽了全力...
I've done everything the way I was supposed to and...

690
01:03:31,690 --> 01:03:34,020
...而现在身边只剩下的 是一瓶松子酒
...all I have to keep me company is a bottle of gin.

691
01:03:34,460 --> 01:03:36,420
你或许也该找个洞洞来下酒
Maybe you should try donuts with your gin.

692
01:03:37,780 --> 01:03:38,790
去你的
Screw you.

693
01:03:41,880 --> 01:03:43,690
夏洛特 你太能演了
Charlotte, you are dramatic.

694
01:03:44,620 --> 01:03:45,910
我差点就当真了
I swear you really almost had me.

695
01:03:45,920 --> 01:03:48,630
一小滴眼泪都要从我眼角边落下了
A tiny tear was beginning to form in the corner of my eye.

696
01:03:49,870 --> 01:03:50,810
别这样了
Now stop it.

697
01:03:51,530 --> 01:03:54,490
你仍旧美得让人窒息啊
You are still breathtakingly beautiful.

698
01:03:55,580 --> 01:03:57,330
只要你肯打起精神从床上爬下来...
When you can be bothered to get up and out of bed...

699
01:03:57,340 --> 01:03:59,510
...不要再事事都怨声连连
...and you stop whimpering about everything for five minutes.

700
01:04:01,070 --> 01:04:03,990
去伦敦吧 改变你的生活
Go to London. Change your life.

701
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:06,370
做女人做得不开心 就别婆婆妈妈的了
If you're not happy being a woman then stop acting like one.

702
01:04:06,740 --> 01:04:08,080
你总有一切问题的答案
You have all the answers.

703
01:04:09,280 --> 01:04:10,900
我没什么答案
No, I don't have any to mention.

704
01:04:11,720 --> 01:04:14,110
你要真这么聪明 何不改变自己的生活
If you're so smart why don't you have something new in your life?

705
01:04:14,410 --> 01:04:15,640
接受斯坦福大学的职位
Take that position at Stanford.

706
01:04:15,650 --> 01:04:17,230
你总是抱怨那所破学校
You complain about that little school

707
01:04:17,240 --> 01:04:18,760
但你其实想去哪都行的
but you could go anywhere you want.

708
01:04:18,770 --> 01:04:20,360
我觉得自己的付出还是有回报的
I think what I've done has been worthwhile.

709
01:04:21,920 --> 01:04:23,350
抱歉 抱歉
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

710
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,580
我不该这么说的
I shouldn't have said that.

711
01:04:26,360 --> 01:04:28,720
尽管很厌恶 但我想我还是会回伦敦的
As much as I dread it, I think I will go back to London.

712
01:04:28,730 --> 01:04:29,780
干嘛要厌恶?
Why do you dread it?

713
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:32,510
我在伦敦时既年轻又新鲜
When I lived in London last I was young.

714
01:04:32,520 --> 01:04:34,180
世界都在我脚下
I was fresh, I was everything.

715
01:04:35,070 --> 01:04:38,360
来美国就像个梦想 像是蛋糕上的糖霜
Coming to America was such a dream, it was the icing on the cake.

716
01:04:39,040 --> 01:04:40,960
回家则是挫败
Going home is defeat.

717
01:04:41,480 --> 01:04:43,780
没有什么事如我所愿的
None of it really worked out the way I'd planned.

718
01:04:44,160 --> 01:04:46,270
大多数事情都是不随人愿的
Most things don't work out the way people plan.

719
01:04:48,670 --> 01:04:49,760
你一直活在过去
You're just living in the past.

720
01:04:49,770 --> 01:04:51,520
你得开始考虑未来了
You need to start thinking about your future.

721
01:04:52,250 --> 01:04:55,070
活在过去就是我的未来
Living in the past is my future.

722
01:04:55,380 --> 01:04:57,820
你就不必如此 你是个男人
It doesn't have to be yours. You're a man.

723
01:04:59,610 --> 01:05:01,730
而且今晚你是个闷蛋男人
And you're a bore tonight.

724
01:05:02,650 --> 01:05:05,790
我们就不能再自怨自艾一小会儿吗
Can't we just feel sorry for ourselves a little bit longer?

725
01:05:06,610 --> 01:05:08,090
再喝一杯吧
Let's have another drink.

726
01:05:08,100 --> 01:05:09,340
算了 我得走了
I don't think so. I have to go.

727
01:05:09,350 --> 01:05:10,140
来陪我出去      求你啦
Come on. Walk me out.        Please, please!

728
01:05:10,150 --> 01:05:13,780
好了 我得走了      不行 这么好玩的
Come on, I have to!        No, this was such fun! No.

729
01:05:22,130 --> 01:05:23,750
我什么时候能再见你?
When will I see you again?

730
01:05:25,720 --> 01:05:29,150
你不是要去英国吗      我绝对不会去的
Aren't you going to England?        I'll never do that!

731
01:05:29,160 --> 01:05:31,100
太花功夫了
It's far too much effort.

732
01:05:31,760 --> 01:05:33,020
再说
Besides,

733
01:05:33,030 --> 01:05:37,060
吉姆也不希望我把你一个人留在洛杉矶
I don't think Jim would want me to leave you here in LA all alone.

734
01:05:37,340 --> 01:05:39,010
别担心我
Don't worry about me. I'll be fine.

735
01:05:39,020 --> 01:05:40,400
我有一切问题的答案 不是吗
I've got all the answers. Remember?

736
01:05:41,230 --> 01:05:42,740
你这周末干嘛
What are you doing this weekend?

737
01:05:44,220 --> 01:05:46,230
很安静地待着吧
I think I might just be very quiet.

738
01:05:48,750 --> 01:05:51,870
你从没对我认真过 对吧 乔治
You never really did take me seriously, did you George?

739
01:05:52,110 --> 01:05:55,360
我试过了 夏莉 记得吗 很早以前
I tried to Charley. Remember? A long time ago.

740
01:05:56,860 --> 01:05:58,660
但没有结果 不是吗
It didn't really work out, did it?

741
01:06:00,990 --> 01:06:01,930
别 夏莉
No, Charley.

742
01:06:09,150 --> 01:06:09,800
晚安
Sleep tight.

743
01:06:52,560 --> 01:06:55,780
帕特里克 来杯啤酒 一包烟
Patrick, a beer and a packet of Lucky Strike, please.

744
01:07:38,830 --> 01:07:39,610
劳驾
Excuse me.

745
01:07:54,850 --> 01:07:55,950
里头太热了
It's too hot in there.

746
01:07:57,230 --> 01:07:57,960
没错
Yes, it is.

747
01:07:58,940 --> 01:08:01,270
来根儿烟?      谢了 我不抽烟
Would you like a cigarette?        No thanks, I don't smoke.

748
01:08:02,490 --> 01:08:06,350
这儿人真多      周六晚上嘛
This place is really crowded.        Well, it is Saturday night.

749
01:08:07,720 --> 01:08:08,570
通常人都很多的
It's usually as bad as this.

750
01:08:08,580 --> 01:08:10,720
大家基本都是在这里搭个人
People normally just stop by and pick someone up

751
01:08:10,730 --> 01:08:12,140
去海边折腾
and then head on down the beach.

752
01:08:13,100 --> 01:08:14,530
嗯 这儿挺狂野的
Yeah. It's pretty wild out there.

753
01:08:15,130 --> 01:08:16,810
很奇怪警察还没来查
I'm surprised the cops don't break it up.

754
01:08:17,320 --> 01:08:20,010
这里总是这样的吗      战后开始
Is it always like that?        Since the war ended.

755
01:08:21,100 --> 01:08:23,310
其实挺棒的 像是邪教聚会
It's pretty great actually. It's kind of pagan.

756
01:08:25,190 --> 01:08:27,250
我叫吉姆      我是乔治
I'm Jim.        I'm George.

757
01:08:27,260 --> 01:08:28,150
幸会 吉姆
Pleased to meet you Jim.

758
01:08:28,160 --> 01:08:30,440
抱歉 我原本是来找朋友的 但我找不着了
I'm sorry, I'm supposed to meet some friends but I can't find them.

759
01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:33,440
我只是出门转转
I just needed to get out of the house

760
01:08:33,450 --> 01:08:35,710
但没禁受住冰啤的诱惑
but the lure of a cold beer got to me.

761
01:08:36,580 --> 01:08:37,630
你住在附近?
Do you live hereby?

762
01:08:37,640 --> 01:08:38,570
在峡谷那儿
Canyon.

763
01:08:39,580 --> 01:08:41,390
住了多久了      38年开始
For how long?        Since 38.

764
01:08:41,400 --> 01:08:43,570
你哪儿来的?      科罗拉多
Where are you from?        Colorado.

765
01:08:44,910 --> 01:08:48,500
我很喜欢这里 离海滩很近・
I really like it here. It's close to beach.

766
01:08:49,680 --> 01:08:51,540
等我退伍后 我估计就会留在这儿了
I think I might stay after I'm discharged.

767
01:08:52,660 --> 01:08:56,060
或许我也有点邪教气息吧
I don't know, maybe I'm a bit of a pagan.

768
01:09:00,300 --> 01:09:01,770
你先请      不
After you.        No.

769
01:09:08,170 --> 01:09:08,860
抱歉
Sorry.

770
01:09:16,690 --> 01:09:18,920
你好啊      嗨
Well, hello.        Hi.

771
01:09:20,620 --> 01:09:22,270
可以给我买杯酒吗
Do you buy me a drink?

772
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:25,290
我有伴了
I think I'm taken.

773
01:09:27,250 --> 01:09:30,270
太可惜了 太可惜了
Too bad, too bad.

774
01:09:32,640 --> 01:09:33,830
还想再来一杯吗
Do you want another beer?

775
01:10:29,350 --> 01:10:32,560
帕特里克 打包威士忌和一包烟
Patrick, a bottle of scotch and a pack of Lucky Strikes to go, please?

776
01:10:42,940 --> 01:10:44,100
帕特里克 不要了
Patrick, cancel that.

777
01:10:55,730 --> 01:10:57,030
你好啊 波特先生
Well, hello Mr. Potter.

778
01:10:58,000 --> 01:10:58,840
你好 先生
Hello, sir.

779
01:11:00,750 --> 01:11:03,080
我们喝什么?      苏格兰威士忌
What are we drinking?        Scotch.

780
01:11:04,200 --> 01:11:04,990
好吧
Okay.

781
01:11:11,180 --> 01:11:12,530
我常来这儿
I come here all the time.

782
01:11:13,180 --> 01:11:15,560
我就住在附近 你知道的
I live just around the corner, but then you knew that.

783
01:11:15,570 --> 01:11:16,940
住在坎弗树路上
On Camphor Tree Lane.

784
01:11:23,490 --> 01:11:24,760
你还带在身上
You're still carrying that around.

785
01:11:27,530 --> 01:11:29,940
人必须对生活赐予的小礼物报以感恩
One must always appreciate life's little gifts.

786
01:11:34,530 --> 01:11:35,840
你在这儿干嘛呢
So, what are you doing here?

787
01:11:36,600 --> 01:11:38,530
出来踩踩单车而已      仅此而已?
Just out for a ride on my bike.        Is that all?

788
01:11:39,550 --> 01:11:40,350
不知道啊
I don't know.

789
01:11:40,750 --> 01:11:41,930
你是在找我吗
Were you looking for me?

790
01:11:42,950 --> 01:11:45,070
可能吧 我不知道
Maybe. I don't know.

791
01:11:45,630 --> 01:11:47,590
我觉得自己脑袋塞满了东西
I feel like my head's stopped up with stuff.

792
01:11:47,600 --> 01:11:48,830
什么东西
What kind of stuff?

793
01:11:48,840 --> 01:11:50,970
譬如您今天在课上说的东西
Like, the stuff you were talking about today in class.

794
01:11:50,980 --> 01:11:52,720
那些完全无关紧要
That is definitely not important.

795
01:11:52,730 --> 01:11:55,210
不 很重要的 您的课很棒
No, it is important. Your class is great.

796
01:11:55,220 --> 01:11:59,230
但我们好像总是在谈论着过去
But somehow we always seem to get stuck talking about the past.

797
01:11:59,860 --> 01:12:01,370
我不关心过去
The past just doesn't matter to me.

798
01:12:01,660 --> 01:12:05,130
那当下呢      我等不及让当下成为过去
The present?        I can't wait for the present to be over.

799
01:12:05,810 --> 01:12:07,120
当下太拖拉了
It's a total drag.

800
01:12:07,730 --> 01:12:10,100
但今晚是个例外
Well, tonight is the exception.

801
01:12:11,650 --> 01:12:12,370
怎么?
What?

802
01:12:13,320 --> 01:12:16,480
今晚 好! 当下 坏!
Tonight, yes! The present, no!

803
01:12:17,060 --> 01:12:18,250
敬今晚
Let's drink to tonight.

804
01:12:18,720 --> 01:12:19,600
敬今晚
Tonight.

805
01:12:22,320 --> 01:12:24,320
如果过去无关紧要 当下又十分拖拉
So if the past doesn't matter and the present is a total drag.

806
01:12:24,330 --> 01:12:25,370
那么未来呢
What about the future?

807
01:12:26,370 --> 01:12:29,010
什么未来 我们或许就要被古巴炸飞了
What future? Cuba might just blow us up.

808
01:12:29,770 --> 01:12:31,050
未来就是死亡啊
Death is the future.

809
01:12:31,520 --> 01:12:33,410
抱歉 我不是故意要说得这么消极的
I'm sorry. I don't mean to be depressing.

810
01:12:33,420 --> 01:12:35,620
不消极 不消极 很真实
It's not depressing. It's not depressing, it's true.

811
01:12:35,630 --> 01:12:38,300
这或许不是近期的将来 但却是我们共同的归宿
It may not be your immediate future but it's what we all share.

812
01:12:39,310 --> 01:12:40,560
死亡就是未来
Death is the future.

813
01:12:41,770 --> 01:12:42,920
我想 你是对的
You're right, I guess.

814
01:12:42,930 --> 01:12:45,770
当人无法再当下获得快乐时...
If one is not enjoying one's present there isn't a great deal to...

815
01:12:45,780 --> 01:12:47,550
...未来的快乐就更是未知的了
...suggest that the future should be any better.

816
01:12:48,410 --> 01:12:49,820
嗯 我过去想过这个
Yeah, I've thought that before.

817
01:12:50,680 --> 01:12:53,970
但问题是 你永远无法预知
But the thing is you just never know.

818
01:12:54,870 --> 01:12:55,760
譬如今晚
Look at tonight.

819
01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:01,360
老实说...
Actually...

820
01:13:02,120 --> 01:13:04,000
...我时常感觉孤单
...I feel really alone most of the time.

821
01:13:04,970 --> 01:13:06,580
是吗      嗯
You do?        Yeah.

822
01:13:07,290 --> 01:13:08,630
我总是有这种感觉
I've always felt this way.

823
01:13:09,070 --> 01:13:11,660
我们孤单一人出世 孤单一人离去
I mean we're born alone, we die alone.

824
01:13:12,350 --> 01:13:13,500
在这世上
And while we're here

825
01:13:13,740 --> 01:13:16,860
我们又被彻底完全地封印在这身体里
we are absolutely, completely sealed in our own bodies.

826
01:13:17,610 --> 01:13:18,600
真够怪的
Really weird.

827
01:13:20,110 --> 01:13:21,850
每每想到这个都会很害怕
Kinda freaks me out to think about it.

828
01:13:22,490 --> 01:13:25,440
我们只能通过自己扭曲的角度
We can only experience the outside world

829
01:13:25,630 --> 01:13:27,390
来体验世界
through our own slanted perception of it.

830
01:13:29,290 --> 01:13:31,040
谁知道你的真是面目呢
Who knows what you're really like?

831
01:13:31,570 --> 01:13:33,370
我看见的只是我认为的你的样子
I just see what I think you're like.

832
01:13:34,050 --> 01:13:36,000
我完全表里如一的
I'm exactly what I appear to be.

833
01:13:38,410 --> 01:13:39,550
只要你走近了看
If you look closely.

834
01:13:46,100 --> 01:13:48,220
你知道吗 人生最有价值的...
You know the only thing that has made the whole thing worthwhile...

835
01:13:50,560 --> 01:13:51,490
几个瞬间
...has been those...

836
01:13:52,500 --> 01:13:53,100
就是当我
...few times

837
01:13:53,110 --> 01:13:56,230
真正和他人交心的时刻
that I've been able to really, truly connect with another human being.

838
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:01,700
我对您有一种预感 先生
I had a hunch about you, sir.

839
01:14:02,150 --> 01:14:03,840
是吗      对
You did?        Yes, sir.

840
01:14:04,490 --> 01:14:06,890
我感觉您一定是个浪漫主义者
I had a hunch you might be a real romantic.

841
01:14:12,390 --> 01:14:15,240
人人都说...
You know, everyone keeps telling you that...

842
01:14:15,250 --> 01:14:18,000
...人老了以后讲积累许多经验
...when you're older, that you'll have all this experience.

843
01:14:18,010 --> 01:14:19,540
仿佛那是件很好的东西
Like it's some great thing.

844
01:14:20,150 --> 01:14:21,130
这都是扯淡
That's a load of shit.

845
01:14:21,590 --> 01:14:23,690
我觉得自己是越来越愚蠢了
I think I've actually just gotten sillier and sillier.

846
01:14:23,950 --> 01:14:25,660
是吗      绝对的
Really?        Absolutely.

847
01:14:25,980 --> 01:14:29,040
所以 所有的经验都是无用的
So, all your experience is useless.

848
01:14:30,300 --> 01:14:31,490
倒也不是
No, I wouldn't say that.

849
01:14:32,830 --> 01:14:34,090
如我们的朋友赫胥黎先生所说
As our friend Mr. Huxley says:

850
01:14:34,100 --> 01:14:35,570
经验不是人遇见的事
Experience is not what happens to a man.

851
01:14:35,580 --> 01:14:37,750
而是人对所遇见事物的反应
It is what a man does with what happens to him.

852
01:14:40,400 --> 01:14:42,260
去游泳吧      好啊
Let's go swimming.        Okay.

853
01:14:43,500 --> 01:14:46,050
怎么      那是个测试
What?        It was a test.

854
01:14:46,260 --> 01:14:48,350
我以为你说变傻的事是在虚张声势...
I thought you were bluffing about being silly so...

855
01:14:48,990 --> 01:14:51,280
...所以我想建议你
...I said to myself I'll suggest

856
01:14:51,290 --> 01:14:53,930
做一件绝对出格的事儿
doing something completely outrageous.

857
01:14:53,990 --> 01:14:56,300
如果你反对 甚至有一丝犹豫
And if he resists, if he even hesitates

858
01:14:56,310 --> 01:14:57,850
那你就是满口胡言
then I know he's full of shit.

859
01:14:59,760 --> 01:15:01,280
看来我不是了 你是吗
Well, I wasn't. Were you?

860
01:15:02,920 --> 01:15:04,190
当然不是
Hell, no!

861
01:15:21,460 --> 01:15:23,550
来吧先生 我帮你下去
Come on sir. I'll help you down.

862
01:15:25,460 --> 01:15:26,200
走
Let's go.

863
01:16:11,830 --> 01:16:13,380
来啊先生
Come on, sir.

864
01:16:45,550 --> 01:16:46,290
先生?
Sir?

865
01:16:47,240 --> 01:16:48,170
先生?
Sir?

866
01:16:58,420 --> 01:16:59,780
差不多了 先生
That's enough for now, sir.

867
01:17:01,410 --> 01:17:03,960
我没事      但我冷了 走吧
I'm fine.        I'm cold. Come on.

868
01:17:16,960 --> 01:17:18,550
可以去您家吗 先生
Can we go back to your place, sir?

869
01:17:19,260 --> 01:17:21,420
当然 不然去哪
Of course. Where else?

870
01:17:22,320 --> 01:17:24,600
不然去哪      你傻啊
Where else.        Are you out of your mind?

871
01:17:25,130 --> 01:17:28,470
怎么了      你不能就这样回家吧
What's the matter?        You can't get home like that!

872
01:17:28,480 --> 01:17:30,180
我们是隐形的 您不知道吗
We're invisible, don't you know that?

873
01:17:32,330 --> 01:17:34,830
先生 他们以后不能让您单独行事
You know sir, they ought not to let you out on your own.

874
01:17:35,070 --> 01:17:36,790
你绝对是个惹麻烦的人
You're liable to get into real trouble.

875
01:17:37,520 --> 01:17:38,460
是我的强项
I excel at it.

876
01:17:39,160 --> 01:17:40,580
您额头出血了
Your forehead is bleeding.

877
01:18:04,300 --> 01:18:06,750
你想洗澡的话 浴室就在走廊尽头
The bathroom is just down the hall if you would like to take a shower.

878
01:18:08,300 --> 01:18:09,890
您不洗个澡吗 先生
Aren't you taking a shower too, sir?

879
01:18:09,900 --> 01:18:12,550
我没事 我们英国人就爱又湿又冷
I'm fine. I'm English. We like to be cold and wet.

880
01:18:13,670 --> 01:18:15,750
我想我们得先处理一下伤口 先生
First, I think that we need to take care of that cut, sir.

881
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:17,190
您有创可贴吗
Do you have any band-aids?

882
01:18:21,160 --> 01:18:24,500
您要去野营吗 先生      我没事 真的
Going camping, sir?        I'm fine, really.

883
01:18:25,560 --> 01:18:27,180
呆在这儿 我马上回来
Stay there. I'll be right back.

884
01:19:09,860 --> 01:19:10,600
坐起来
Sit up.

885
01:19:13,040 --> 01:19:14,100
仰头
Tilt your head back.

886
01:19:38,590 --> 01:19:40,690
先生 这回您恐怕不能以迷幻药...
Well sir, I'm afraid this time you don't have...

887
01:19:40,700 --> 01:19:43,080
...作为您贴创可贴的原因了
...the excuse of mescaline to explain your band-aid.

888
01:19:45,520 --> 01:19:47,560
你该把湿衣服脱下来
I think we should get you out of those wet clothes.

889
01:19:50,590 --> 01:19:51,390
遵命
Yes, sir.

890
01:21:21,020 --> 01:21:22,930
不会冷吧      我挺好
You're not too cold?        I'm great.

891
01:21:24,100 --> 01:21:27,100
想来一杯吗      啤酒吧 如果您有的话
Would you like a drink?        A beer, sir. If you have one.

892
01:21:27,110 --> 01:21:29,360
恐怕我就只有这个了
I'm afraid that's all we have.

893
01:21:29,900 --> 01:21:31,050
两杯啤酒 马上就来
Two beers coming up.

894
01:21:45,220 --> 01:21:46,310
您一个人住在这里吗 先生
You live here all by yourself, sir?

895
01:21:46,320 --> 01:21:47,020
现在是了
I do now.

896
01:21:47,870 --> 01:21:50,280
曾经是和一个朋友同住 他是个建筑师
I used to share this place with a friend. He was an architect.

897
01:21:50,970 --> 01:21:54,280
我们这年纪的人做梦都想要有这房子的设施啊
Man, guys my age dream about the kind of setup you've got here.

898
01:21:54,290 --> 01:21:56,960
夫复何求啊
I mean, what more can you want?

899
01:21:56,970 --> 01:22:00,170
可以独自生活 来去自如
You get to be left alone and come and go as you please.

900
01:22:02,110 --> 01:22:03,880
这就是你的理想生活吗
Is that's your idea of the perfect life?

901
01:22:03,890 --> 01:22:05,950
怎么 先生 您不相信吗
What's the matter, sir? Don't you believe me?

902
01:22:06,460 --> 01:22:08,430
如果你这么热爱独自一人的生活...
If you're so keen on the idea living by yourself...

903
01:22:08,440 --> 01:22:10,130
...洛伊斯对你来说又是什么呢
...where does Lois fit into this plan?

904
01:22:10,590 --> 01:22:13,380
洛伊斯?这关她什么事?
Lois? What's she got to do with anything?

905
01:22:14,160 --> 01:22:16,190
我感觉你俩是一对的
I got the impression that you and she were together.

906
01:22:19,280 --> 01:22:22,830
谈不上 她挺酷的...
Not really. She is kind of cool and...

907
01:22:22,960 --> 01:22:24,250
...我们是好朋友但...
...we're good friends but...

908
01:22:26,940 --> 01:22:30,150
您真正想问的是我俩有没有上过床吧
I think what you really want to ask me is if we sleep together.

909
01:22:31,240 --> 01:22:33,200
上过吗      上过 有一次
And do you?        We did. Once.

910
01:22:33,210 --> 01:22:34,530
怎么只有一次
Why only once?

911
01:22:35,200 --> 01:22:37,260
我没说"只有一次" 是"有一次"
I didn't say only once, I said once.

912
01:22:38,650 --> 01:22:40,890
拜托 我现在最不想说的就洛伊斯了
Come on, the last thing I want to talk about right now is Lois.

913
01:22:41,660 --> 01:22:42,650
现在几点了
What time is it?

914
01:22:45,460 --> 01:22:46,990
我的表似乎停了
My watch seems to have stopped.

915
01:22:54,240 --> 01:22:55,800
你想让我走了吗
Do you want me to go?

916
01:22:56,690 --> 01:22:58,850
开玩笑 再去拿两杯啤酒来
You must be kidding. Go, get us another beer.

917
01:23:00,760 --> 01:23:01,870
这是命令吗 先生
Is that an order, sir?

918
01:23:04,220 --> 01:23:05,450
当然
You're damn right it is.

919
01:23:16,610 --> 01:23:17,610
可悲啊
Pathetic.

920
01:23:19,760 --> 01:23:20,890
您说什么了吗 先生
Did you say something, sir?

921
01:23:25,500 --> 01:23:26,620
你为什么来这儿
Why are you here?

922
01:23:29,230 --> 01:23:34,330
你为什么去办公室 向秘书要我的地址
Why did you get to the office and ask secretary for my address?

923
01:23:36,370 --> 01:23:40,560
我只想在学校以外的地方见到您
I just wanted to see you someplace other than school.

924
01:23:41,610 --> 01:23:42,390
为什么
Why?

925
01:23:46,040 --> 01:23:47,620
有时我觉得自己疯了
Sometimes I think I'm crazy

926
01:23:47,630 --> 01:23:49,760
因为我看到的世界和众人不同
cause I see things so differently than everyone else.

927
01:23:51,030 --> 01:23:52,370
我感觉可以向您倾诉
I feel like I can talk to you.

928
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:57,050
老实说先生 我今天很担心您
To be honest sir, I was also worried about you today.

929
01:24:01,760 --> 01:24:02,460
我吗
Me?

930
01:24:03,830 --> 01:24:05,050
有什么好担心的
What's to be worried about?

931
01:24:06,680 --> 01:24:07,390
我没事
I'm fine.

932
01:24:16,900 --> 01:24:17,590
我...
I'm...

933
01:24:19,400 --> 01:24:20,340
我没事
I'm fine.

934
01:26:58,020 --> 01:27:02,680
我人生中 只有几个醍醐灌顶的瞬间
A few times in my life I've had moments of absolute clarity.

935
01:27:05,040 --> 01:27:07,010
那短暂的瞬间里...
When for a few brief seconds...

936
01:27:07,910 --> 01:27:10,130
...寂静淹没了嘈杂...
...the silence drowns out the noise...

937
01:27:10,140 --> 01:27:13,400
...我更能够感觉 而不是思考
...and I can feel rather than think.

938
01:27:14,310 --> 01:27:16,560
一切都显得那么明晰...
And things seem so sharp...

939
01:27:17,310 --> 01:27:19,290
世界都显得那么清澈...
And the world seems so fresh...

940
01:27:20,750 --> 01:27:23,470
...仿佛一切都物归原主了
...as though it had all just come into existence.

941
01:27:43,100 --> 01:27:45,360
但我永远无法维持这样的瞬间
I can never make these moments last.

942
01:27:46,220 --> 01:27:47,520
我牢牢抓住它们...
I cling to them...

943
01:27:47,530 --> 01:27:49,210
...但如同万事万物 它们都消逝了
...but like everything they fade.

944
01:27:51,700 --> 01:27:53,440
我一直活在这几个时刻当中
I've lived my live on these moments.

945
01:27:55,190 --> 01:27:56,810
但它们又将我推回当下...
They pull me back to the present...

946
01:27:59,070 --> 01:27:59,680
然后我意识到
...and I realize that

947
01:27:59,680 --> 01:28:04,020
一切都是按照命中注定的轨道行驶
everything is exactly the way it was meant to be.

948
01:30:18,140 --> 01:30:21,590
就这样 袭来
And just like that it came.

